Government says dam levels in the province have dropped to an average of 55%. CAPE TOWN - The Western Cape Government expects the drought to persist into next year.The Provincial Local Government Department says the dam levels in the province have dropped to an average of 55%, lower than the same period last year.The department s James-Brent Styan says: It s already bad but we are managing it like we have over the past year. We would certainly have been in a crisis situation, there s no doubt about that. We re not happy or comfortable yet. Some areas are better than others. The City of Cape Town this week urged residents to intensify their water saving efforts.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)